task.summary: Default task
Put testlib folder in a package in the test folder. Marked test folder as test, not source.
Fix raiseTo(). Re-arranged test code again.
Fix in Coef.simply to handle 0-len term arrays. Fix in Coef.times to ignore empty terms (terms that exist with a coef of 0 and empty Atom array).
Fix bug where Atoms array was set to null instead of Atom[0]. It had downstream effects on of(), times() and plus().
Fix where trailing + appearing in poly.toString() and where there would be a +- instead of just a -.
Updated Coef.smartInsert and wrote a unit test.
Unit tests for Coef reduce, pop, push and Term reduce, pop, push.
Fully port to Term.reduce() instead of simplify in the Coef object.
Redid sorting of terms within a coef to be: constant terms go last, sort abstract terms alphanumerically, ignoring constant coef.
Fixed error where Atoms that had power 0 were messing up the sort order.
Got rid of random tests in PolynomialTest
Got rid of isLessThan tests in TermTests because the rules of sorting have changed.
Changed or deleted place, insert and times tests now that the coef auto-reduces.
updated class diagram
Ignore the string compare tests in paramaterized suite because the order of terms will be different.
Ignore the string compare tests in paramaterized suite because the order of terms will be different.
Ignore the string compare tests in paramaterized suite because the order of terms will be different.
Delete commented out code, unused iZeroTerm method and renamed Term.smartInsert to Term.insert.
Remove Coef.smartInsert.
made @author note
updated class diagram
Removed Term.isLessThan and updated class diagram.
Updated Java doc comments with @since tag and generated new Javadocs.
Updated README Changelog regarding sort order of terms within a Coef.
Fix link to Javadocs
Re-made Javadocs in out/html folder and Fixed link to Javadocs
Remove all Javadocs and start over.
Re-generated Javadocs in out/html
recompiled, new jar
recompiled, new jar
recompiled, new jar that only has the 4 classes, not the test classes. Marked test folders as Tests.
Minor fix to Polynomial.toString to avoid strings like X+-1.0. Now it will be X-1.0.
Hiding tests from jar
Fixed bug in constructor with just a degree that did not correctly create all the coefs.
Get the constant coefficient of a given term. Throws assertion error if the coeffiecient is not a constant. e.g. it has variables like (2.0a_1)X
Refreshed JavaDocs and class diagrams.
Properly marked @deprecated methods as @Deprecated.
Fixed evaluateToNumber
restructured test package structure. made sure they don't appear in JAR.
Updated README
added polyfun.jar to the workspace
fix to getConstantCoefAt for when there is no Coef. Also made evaluateWith(x) to see if that name feels more natural.
Made getCoefficientFor(int xTerm) as the new name for getConstantCoefAt(int degree) to see if that name feels more natural.
New method getCoefficientArray that is essentially the inverse of Polynomial(new double[]{1,2, 3}) - it gets the coefs back out of the poly.
reran javadocs because of the new methods.
marked methods with inferior names as deprecated to encourage use of newly named ones. also, refactored isPlottable.
updates javadocs
Fixed bug in getCoefficientAtTerm(int) and renamed. Marked previous versions as deprecated and reran javadocs.
Changed getCoefficientAtTerm to return 1 if the coeffient is not a constant, e.g. b.
